article.headline: Florida 94, Florida Gulf Coast 60
article.story: MARK LONG AP Sports Writer GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Alex Tyus and Walter Hodge scored 19 points apiece and Florida beat Florida Gulf Coast 94-60 on Wednesday night. The Gators, who fell out of the Associated Press poll this week after losing to rival Florida State, improved to 21-0 against teams from the Atlantic Sun Conference under coach Billy Donovan. This one was close for a while. The Eagles (2-6) were up 28-27 late in the first half, thanks mostly to Reed Baker's five 3-pointers. But the Gators (7-2) pounded the ball inside using their height advantage, and pulled away after the break. Florida, which opened up a 30-point lead with about five minutes to play, finished with a 44-32 edge on the boards. Baker was scoreless in the second half and finished with 15 points. Kyle Marks added 14 points and nine rebounds for Florida Gulf Coast.
